# 8. SGB construction based on Mash distance

## 8.1 Collect MAGs for SGB clustering

```bash
# Activate the conda environment containing Mash
conda activate mash

# Copy all MAGs into the SGB analysis directory
cp Binning/${sample}_metawrap_metabat2/metabat2_bins/*.fa \
   SGBs/MAGs/
```

**Explanation:**  
This step collects MAG files for SGB clustering.

In this version, all MAGs are copied into the SGB directory. For more rigorous analysis, only high-quality or medium-quality MAGs should be selected based on CheckM2 results.

---

## 8.2 Build Mash sketches for all MAGs

```bash
# Build Mash sketches
mash sketch \
  -o SGBs/MAGs_sketch \
  -k 21 \
  -s 10000 \
  SGBs/MAGs/*.fa
```

**Explanation:**  
Mash converts genome sequences into compact sketches for rapid genome distance calculation.

Important parameters:

```bash
-k 21
```

This sets the k-mer size to 21.

```bash
-s 10000
```

This sets the sketch size to 10,000.

Main output file:

```bash
SGBs/MAGs_sketch.msh
```

---

## 8.3 Calculate pairwise Mash distances

```bash
# Calculate pairwise Mash distances among MAGs
mash dist \
  SGBs/MAGs_sketch.msh \
  SGBs/MAGs_sketch.msh \
  -p ${threads} \
  > SGBs/mash_distances.tab
```

**Explanation:**  
This step calculates pairwise Mash distances among all MAGs.

Main output file:

```bash
SGBs/mash_distances.tab
```

The third column of this file represents the Mash distance between two MAGs.

---

## 8.4 Extract similar MAG pairs

```bash
# Extract MAG pairs with Mash distance <= 0.05
# This threshold approximately corresponds to genome similarity >= 95%
awk '$3 <= 0.05 {print $1"\t"$2}' \
  SGBs/mash_distances.tab \
  > SGBs/similar_pairs.tsv
```

**Explanation:**  
This step extracts MAG pairs with Mash distance ≤ 0.05.

This threshold is approximately equivalent to 95% genome similarity and is often used as a rough species-level boundary.

Main output file:

```bash
SGBs/similar_pairs.tsv
```

Note: Mash-based clustering is fast but approximate. For high-quality publication analysis, FastANI or dRep-based ANI clustering is recommended.

